AB  - We introduce international capital mobility into the Harris-Todaro model and examine the effectiveness of some policy tools. The main message is such that a wage subsidy in manufacturing and a tariff are no longer effective to improve welfare, while a wage subsidy in agriculture remains valid under the assumption of international capital mobility. This is in sharp contrast to the result obtained for the original Harris-Todaro model.
