AB  - This paper investigates the determinants of oligopsony power exerted by coffee exporters in Haiti. It develops and estimates a two-equation model with cross-parameter restrictions: one equation for the Lerner index of oligopsony and the other for the residual supply function facing exporters. Empirical results indicate that both institutional arrangements and domestic market conditions have significantly shaped oligopsony power.
ER  - 
